					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">By the way. Even though MMC3 uses $2000 sized banks, there's no reason you can't program in $4000 sized chunks, as long as you set both the $8000-9fff bank and the $a000-bfff banks every time you switch PRG banks.<br /><br />That would make it similar to MMC1 or UxROM boards.<br /><br />MMC3 is still better than both, because of the scanline counter IRQ, which can do parallax scrolling (for example).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
