				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Or with a suitable assembler, you can all but ignore bank boundaries altogether. Say you switch bank y into window 6 ($8000) and bank y+1 into window 7 ($A000), and y can be either even or odd. Then you can access anything in ROM that doesn't cross two bank boundaries. <em>The Curse of Possum Hollow</em> does this with its compressed tiles and background map streams.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

